    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Explanation: P0600"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "P0600",
      "text": "DTC P0600: ECU internal communication error"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2146_3.0_jpn_11231349_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If an abnormality occurs in the communication between the driver IC with the failure diagnosis function and the CPU, and the CPU is unable to acquire failure diagnosis information from each driver for a set period of time or longer, the PGM-FI ECU judges that a failure has occurred and stores the DTC."
    },
